that at a fixed age, smallish gaps are sensitive mostly to\nthe mass of the subhalo, while gaps formed by subhalo flybys with a low\nrelative velocity, or when the stream and subhalo move parallel, are degenerate\nto the encounter parameters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Nov 2020 19:24:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-19"}
